article.headline: Air Force 69, UC Davis 57
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Tom Fow had a career-high 30 points and Mike McLain added a career-best 12 points and nine rebounds to lead Air Force to a 69-57 win over UC Davis on Tuesday night. Fow doubled his previous career high of 15 points, which had come in the Falcons' (6-4) last game, by connecting on 8 of 13 shots from the field. He was 6 of 9 from 3-point range. The Aggies (3-8) cut Air Force's lead to 54-51 with 4:43 remaining, but that was as close as they would get. The Falcons outscored them 15-6 the rest of the way to seal the victory. Dominic Calegari and Mark Payne led the Aggies with 14 points each. The Falcons trailed by as many as seven points in a seesaw first half, but took a 29-27 lead into the locker room on a buzzer-beating 3-pointer by McLain.
